  "texts": [
    "This better corresponds to continual learning with multiple tasks in nature, because, for example, if humans learn to perform two different tasks, they typically use one brain and one pair of hands (that is, the whole network is shared), as they do not have two different pairs of hands (that is, humans share the output layers across tasks).",
    "Task 1 was trained for four iterations, task 2 was trained for four iterations, and the training continued until a total of 84 iterations was reached.",
    "After each iteration, error on the test set of each task was meas ured as 'test error'.",
    "In Fig. 4e, the mean of test error of both tasks during training of Fig.",
    "4d at different learning rates is reported."
